dataIdInfo.suppInfo: This linear feature class describes the location of the rabbit fence in south eastern Queensland. The feature class was built from GPS points captured on a Garmin GPS in 2008. It was revised in 2016 using the most currently available imagery available from the SISP subscription service. The fence itself is maintained by the Darling Downs / Morton Rabbit Board.

dataqual.logic:
The DDMRB fence was surveyed using GPS by Mark Ridge from DDMRB in 2005. Craig Hunter from DPI&F Dalby sent the layer to Brisbane in May 2008. The layer was checked against the previous Rabbit fence layer and found to be geometrically different. The Layer was edited to remove errors, and re-attributed as follows: Re-projected from WGS84 to GDA94.
In ArcEdit mode, merged all features to a single polyline. Then edited line as follows: Used explode to identify line gaps and eroneous 'squiggle' lines, and lines that over-lapped. Manually joined gaps using 'snapping', then checked that gap had been closed using Explode ('no multi-part features selected' message would show if gap closed completely). Deleted eroneous 'squiggle' lines, and lines that over-lapped.
Attributes TOPNET: Attributed line according to Rabbit Barrier fence.shp with top-net / no top/net attributes. LG1 and LG2: Attributed line according to LGA_Oct08.shp, LGA1 = LGAs to north and east of Barrier fence; LGA2 = LGAs to south and west of Barrier fence. Length_Km: Re-calculated length in Km's using calculate geometry tool in ArcGIS.
Renamed DDMRRB fence trk joined.shp to RabbitBarrierFence_Nov08, saved: L:\SpatialStorage\ControlLines_MgtAreas\QLD_ControlLines. Archived all other fence layers to L:\SpatialStorage\ControlLines_MgtAreas\QLD_ControlLines\Archives
Moya Calvert November 2008

dataLineage.statement: The linear feature class was originally created in November 2008, from field data collection of GPS points using a Garmin GPS (accuracy 5-10m). The linear features have been updated using orthorectified 10 to 30cm aerial imagery captured in 2013.

report.measDesc: This dataset was compiled using GPS in 2008, which has a known accuracy limitation of 5-10m. The fence was upated using best avaiable imagery in 2016, including orthophotos and SPOT imagery. As such, the dataset may contain some spatial errors.

ConResult.conExpl: The dataset is to a standard determined as fit for the purpose for which it was collected.
